Rating: 3
I recommend the version of this in Rib Eye Steaks with Bearnaise Butter (Bon Appetit 99). It calls for reducing the shallots with white wine before compounding the butter, which intensifies the flavor. But this recipe inspired the addition of a squeeze of lemon which makes a big difference. Overall, though, 2 similar ideas, and it was delicious over a pepper crusted filet (not to mention a lot less agony than bearnaise sauce).

