Rating: 4
I made this, for my husband's birthday dinner. I used 1 1/2 inch thick sirloin steaks. I could not grill, and do not own a grill pan. I broiled the steaks to a lovely medium rare, and topped with the butter. Served with steamed asparagus, boiled new potatoes, and sauted mushrooms. The dinner was a big hit. My husband said it was better than anything he could have gotten in a restaurant.

Rating: 2
I agree with Ridge Manor, FL. It's quite likely in my opinion that if you have four 1" ribeyes, that ALONE without an herb butter, they will be excellent. Maybe it's not the recipe for something special, as much as 4 excellent steaks with special enhancements or not. Still, it's easy enough to put together, so I would consider making it again. I just wouldn't expect great reviews unless I began with great steaks; and I'd assume it was perhaps the STEAKS which deserved the applause, moreso than the bearnaise butter making them great.

